com.apriori.reflect

Class TypeAnnotationChecker.Builder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.apriori.reflect.TypeAnnotationChecker.Builder
  • Enclosing interface:
    TypeAnnotationChecker

    public static class TypeAnnotationChecker.Builder
extends Object
    A builder for creating instances of TypeAnnotationChecker. This provides a simple API for defining assignment compatibility of type annotations. Assignability is defined in terms of pairs of annotation types: an assignment target and an assignment source. Annotations with fields are further checked for value compatibility by checking that the values on a target annotation match those of a source annotation.

    It is valid to pass null as an annotation type to the builder methods. A null type annotation corresponds to an unannotated type, or an "unqualified" type. A null type is considered to have the same structure as a non-null annotation that has no methods.

        public TypeAnnotationChecker.Builder equivalent(Class<? extends Annotation> anno1,
                                                Class<? extends Annotation> anno2)
        Defines an equivalence relationship between the given two type annotations. The structure of the annotations (method names and their return values) must be the same.
        Parameters:
        anno1 - a type annotation
        anno2 - another type annotation
        Returns:
        this, for method chaining
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the two types do not have compatible structure or if the two given types are the same type
        IllegalStateException - if introducing the relationship would form a cycle in the relationships already defined in this builder

      • equivalent

        public TypeAnnotationChecker.Builder equivalent(Class<? extends Annotation> anno1,
                                                Class<? extends Annotation> anno2,
                                                Map<String,String> attributeMap)
        Defines an equivalence relationship between the given two type annotations. The signatures of the annotations' methods must be the same, though the names can vary. The given map defines the mapping in structure, from method names in the first annotation to corresponding method names in the second. The map must be invertible -- e.g. the mappings must be 1-to-1 (multiple keys with the same value are not permitted).
        Parameters:
        anno1 - a type annotation
        anno2 - another type annotation
        attributeMap - a map of method names in anno1 to their corresponding method name in anno2
        Returns:
        this, for method chaining
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the two types do not have compatible structure, if the two given types are the same type, or if the given mapping is invalid (e.g. missing a method, has keys and values that do not correspond to valid methods, or does not have 1-to-1 mappings)
        IllegalStateException - if introducing the relationship would form a cycle in the relationships already defined in this builder

      • assignable

        public TypeAnnotationChecker.Builder assignable(Class<? extends Annotation> from,
                                                Class<? extends Annotation> to)
        Defines an assignability relationship (or subtype relationship) between the given two type annotations. The first type (or source) is assignable to the second type (or target); it can be interpreted as the first type being a subtype of the second type. The structure of the annotations (method names and their return values) must be the compatible: all methods present in the target type are present (with the same return type) in the source type. The source type may have methods that do not appear in the target type, but not vice versa.
        Parameters:
        from - a source annotation
        to - a target annotation
        Returns:
        this, for method chaining
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the two types do not have compatible structure or if the two given types are the same type
        IllegalStateException - if introducing the relationship would form a cycle in the relationships already defined in this builder

      • assignable

        public TypeAnnotationChecker.Builder assignable(Class<? extends Annotation> from,
                                                Class<? extends Annotation> to,
                                                Map<String,String> attributeMap)
        Defines an assignability relationship (or subtype relationship) between the given two type annotations. The first type (or source) is assignable to the second type (or target); it can be interpreted as the first type being a subtype of the second type. The signatures of the annotations' methods must be the compatible: all methods present in the target type must have a corresponding method with the same return type in the source type. The source type may have methods that do not appear in the target type, but not vice versa. The given map defines the mapping in structure, from method names in the source annotation to corresponding method names in the target. The map must be invertible -- e.g. the mappings must be 1-to-1 (multiple keys with the same value are not permitted).
        Parameters:
        from - a source annotation
        to - a target annotation
        attributeMap - a map of method names in from to their corresponding method name in to
        Returns:
        this, for method chaining
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the two types do not have compatible structure, if the two given types are the same type, or if the given mapping is invalid (e.g. missing a mapping for the target annotation, has keys and values that do not correspond to valid methods, or does not have 1-to-1 mappings)
        IllegalStateException - if introducing the relationship would form a cycle in the relationships already defined in this builder
